<div class="row report-section-container verbal-section-performance">
  <div class="col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
    <div class="report-section-container-inner">
      <div class="report-section-heading">verbal section performance</div>
      <div class="report-section-content">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-3 col-xs-3">
            <div class="box-1">
              <div>
                your score
              </div>
              <div>
                <%= verbal_score = @paper.calculate_score %>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="box-2">
              <%= @paper.percentile.ordinalize %> Percentile
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-head">
              Explanation
            </div>
            <div class="explanation-text">
              Your <%= gmat_trademark %> Verbal score is <%= verbal_score %>. This score is better than <%= @paper.percentile.ordinalize %>% of <%= gmat_trademark %> Exam scores recorded in the past three years. (As per <%= gmat_trademark %> report)
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-6 col-xs-6">
            <div class="graph-content">
              <div id="verbal-section-performance-graph" style="height: 234px; background-color: transparent;"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-3 col-xs-3">
            <div class="content">
              <div class="font-18 bold">MEAN SCORE : 26.80</div>
              <div class="font-16 bold color-green">44th percentile</div>
              <div class="explanation-head">
                Explanation
              </div>
              <div class="explanation-text">
                <p>
                  The three year mean <%= gmat_trademark %> Verbal score is 26.8. This score is better than 44% of <%= gmat_trademark %> Exam scores recorded in the past three years.
                </p>
                <p class="note-p">
                  <span class="note">Note:</span> <span class="note-text"><%= gmat_trademark %> scores are valid for five years. Even though your score won't change, your percentile ranking may change when compared with a newer pool of applicants. Shifts tend to be gradual over long periods of time.</span>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
